<TITLE> New RPO amendment eases registration rules </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 6 (bdnews24.com) - The interim cabinet on Monday approved a second amendment to the Representation of the People (amendment) Ordinance 2008, allowing political parties to register with draft party constitutions. In this case, the party will have to submit a ratified constitution to the Election Commission within six months from the first sitting of the ninth parliament, the chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told reporters after the cabinet meeting chaired by chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed. According to the new amendment, potential candidtes who have been defaulting on loans and utility bills, must pay up 15 days ahead of submission of nomination papers. The deadline has been greatly reduced from the previous six months ahead of submission of papers. The maximum election expenditure of a party has been set at Tk 1.5 lakh per constituency. Maximum expenditure was previously set per 300, 200 and 100 constituencies at Tk 4.5 crore, Tk 3 crore and Tk 75 lakh. bdnews
